<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.415C/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">South</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-11T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>35. Your despatch 678, April 2, and telegram 50, April 28, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <p>You may inform Minister for Foreign Affairs that Government of United
                            States accepts with thanks invitation courteously extended.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
